rosing cholangitis","Primary biliary cholangitis","Choledocholithiasis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EJaundice can be classified based on where bilirubin metabolism is disrupted:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPre-hepatic causes: increased bilirubin production overwhelms normal liver function (e.g. \u003Cstrong\u003Ehaemolytic anaemia\u003C/strong\u003E)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EHepatic causes: liver cell dysfunction impairs bilirubin conjugation (e.g. \u003Cstrong\u003Eviral hepatitis\u003C/strong\u003E, cirrhosis)\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPost-hepatic causes: obstruction of bile flow after the liver (e.g. \u003Cstrong\u003Eprimary sclerosing cholangitis\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Eprimary biliary cholangitis\u003C/strong\u003E, \u003Cstrong\u003Echoledocholithiasis\u003C/strong\u003E)\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EViral hepatitis causes inflammation and damage to hepatocytes, impairing their ability to process bilirubin, making it a hepatic cause of jaundice.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Jaundice can be classified as pre-hepatic, hepatic, or post-hepatic based on the site of bilirubin metabolism disruption","Gilbert\u0027s syndrome and viral hepatitis are examples of hepatic causes of jaundice","Primary sclerosing cholangitis and primary biliary cholangitis are post-hepatic causes of jaundice"],"references":["Joseph A, Samant H. Jaundice. 2023 Aug 8. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31334972","amada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Gasmi B, Kleiner DE. Liver Histology: Diagnostic and Prognostic Features. Clin Liver Dis. 2020 Feb;24(1):61-74. doi: